surement. Then, we focus on nearby events. We simulated sources\nsimilar to GW150914 and GW151226 and check how well their parameters can be\nmeasured by various networks. Here too we find that the main difference is a\nbetter estimation of the sky position, although even a single triangular-shaped\nthird-generation detector can estimate their sky position to 1~deg$^2$ or\nbetter.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 20 Apr 2018 23:52:59 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 24 Apr 2018 05:15:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-07-25"}
